title: App Features
text: I enjoy most app features like reposts and being able to live stream. But I am disappointed that many people have access to features while others don’t. For example, the slideshow feature. This is the feature in which you can have photos but you can manually swipe through the photos yourself. I don’t know if it’s only accessible to some phones or what, I’ve complained over it many of times and I used to have it but then it disappeared! It’s the one feature I want which will make me upload content more.

title: Looks great but missing critical features
text: In its current state, I think it would be preferable to just publish the iPad version of the app for Vision Pro. Several features are missing, and the biggest omission is direct messages, which are a critical feature that really shouldn’t have been overlooked. That being said it looks great, and you can still browse all of the TikTok content you like using your own account. I’ve been enjoying scrolling through videos while washing dishes- where before i would get water all over my phone. Assuming the platform survives the current congressional climate, this app will probably be full-featured and lovely in no time.
